Preheat your oven to 220°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges
(no need to peel). Pop onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

While the wedges cook, put the @water{100%ml} in a large #saucepan{} on high
heat. Add the @BBQ sauce{64%g}, @cider vinegar{15%ml}, @chipotle paste{20%g}
and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir well to combine and bring to a
simmer.

Stir in the @diced chicken breast{260%g} and bring to a boil, then lower the
heat to medium and cover with a #lid{}. Simmer until the chicken is cooked and
tender, ~{15-20%minutes}, stirring halfway and lowering the heat if necessary.

Once cooked, remove the saucepan from the heat and transfer the chicken to a
board with a #slotted spoon{}. Roughly chop the chicken.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its
> packaging. The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While the chicken simmers, trim and thinly slice the @spring onion{1}. Trim and
grate the @carrot{1}(grated) (no need to peel). Grate the @mature cheddar
cheese{60%g}.

Drain and rinse the @black beans{1/2%tin} in a #sieve{}. Pop half the beans
into a medium #bowl{} and roughly mash with a #fork{}.

Once the chicken is cooked and out of your saucepan, add the black beans (both
whole and mashed) and carrot to the remaining sauce in the pan.

Stir everything together, then boil vigorously on high heat until reduced to a
thick sauce, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> TIP: Stir frequently and cook for a bit longer if you need to - you want it
> really thick!

Once thickened, stir in the chopped chicken and simmer for ~{2%minutes}, then
remove from the heat. Taste and add @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

When the wedges are ready, transfer them to an #ovenproof dish{}. Spoon the
chicken and sauce on top.

Sprinkle over the cheese, then bake in the oven until golden and bubbling,
~{5-6%minutes}.

When ready, remove from the oven and sprinkle over the spring onion to finish.

Enjoy!

> Step 3 MOD: If you've chosen to get diced chicken breast instead of thigh,
> cook the recipe in the same way.